			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Metallurgical silicon is a hard, brittle crystalline solid with a blue-grey metallic luster. It is a tetravalent metalloid and semiconductor, and a member of group 14 in the periodic table. The silicon is treated to remove impurities such as calcium and aluminum. Upgraded Metallurgical-Grade (UMG) silicon has raised interest as an alternative material for silicon solar cells due to its low cost, low environmental impact and low CAPEX.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">冶金硅是一种硬而脆的结晶固体，具有蓝灰色金属光泽。它是一种四价金属和半导体，属于元素周期表中的第 14 族。硅经过处理可去除钙和铝等杂质。升级冶金级（UMG）硅因其低成本、低环境影响和低资本支出，已成为硅太阳能电池的替代材料，引起了人们的兴趣。</common:generalComment>
